# creating-ui
---
description: When creating a UI, creating the components in components/ui is your priority. You should also create your own components. Depending on the situation, they can be in the components/ui folder or the components folder.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
# event
---
description: Triggering will be done through events. All triggering should be done through the event system.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
# package-manager
---
description: Use npm as the package manager.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
# dont-install-package
---
description: Do not install libraries unless absolutely necessary. Only use external libraries when critically needed.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
# enums
---
description: Keys must never be hardcoded as strings. They should be added to @enums.ts and used from there.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
# service
---
description: No service may use its own axios.get directly. All endpoints must be defined in @internalEndpoints.ts or @externalEndpoints.ts, and then used via @internalServices.ts or @externalServices.ts.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
# localization
---
description: All application texts will be localized using JSON files inside the localization directory, with translations written per language. These will be managed through @index.ts.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
# theme
---
description: All theme colors, variations, and sizing will be managed from @ThemeContext.tsx. These values will remain static, except for light and dark mode toggling.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
# components
---
description: The components/ui folder will only contain simple UI elements. More complex components will be placed in the main components folder. If a specific area contains multiple related components, they will be grouped in a dedicated subfolder.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
# types
---
description: All interfaces will be placed inside @types.d.ts. Since this file is global, there's no need to import or export them.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

